comments.body: Current pulfalight prod boxes have 2 CPUs, 16 GB of memory, and a 40 GB hard drive each. Both are on hosts in `b` datacenter, so new VMs should go on hosts in `a` datacenter.
There's a good chance that CPU caps out well before RAM and we can lower the RAM there. Let me slam the servers real quick and see.

Sieging it as hard as I could I couldn't get memory to rise above like 4GB:

![Screen Shot 2022-03-09 at 1 19 51 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2806645/157537966-8ed4fa8e-3ee0-4654-a430-fbf935acd020.png)
They're now all 11-12G. No one did anything as far as we know.
It is currently on rails 5.2, so I am closing this ticket.
